1) Transmission. Influenza viruses and SARS-CoV-2 predominantly spread via respiratory droplets that are transmitted during close community contact. Consequently, social distancing policies designed to limit COVID-19 transmission are also effective against influenza (
 
  3
 ). The corollary is that if COVID-19 cases begin to spike in the fall of 2020, retightening of social distancing measures could allay early spread of influenza to flatten the case-rate curves for both diseases.
